The failure of the ignition switch can cause the vehicle to stall or shut off while driving, leading to a loss of power steering, power brakes, and airbags, which can increase the risk of accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or shuts off while driving

often without warning; the ignition switch needs to be removed and reinserted to restart the vehicle; the vehicle may experience intermittent electrical shutdowns; the battery warning light may illuminate; the check engine light may be illuminated.
